<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="497" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1781,2022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1781,1806]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body greenish. Head and thorax faintly marked stramineous. External characters as in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Webb &amp; Vilbaste, 1994)" authorityName="Webb &amp; Vilbaste" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Webb &amp; Vilbaste" baseAuthorityYear="1994" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Balclutha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bispinosa">
<emphasis box="[1294,1436,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">B. bispinosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Webb, M. D. &amp; Vilbaste, J." box="[158,426,1817,1842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" pagination="56 - 86" refId="ref6867" refString="Webb, M. D. &amp; Vilbaste, J. (1994) Review of the leafhopper genus Balclutha Kirkaldy in the Oriental Region (Insecta: Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 56, 56 - 86." type="journal article" year="1994">Webb &amp; Vilbaste, 1994</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1781,2022]" box="[199,671,1853,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">
Description from 
<bibRefCitation author="Webb, M. D. &amp; Vilbaste, J." box="[398,671,1853,1878]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497" pagination="56 - 86" refId="ref6867" refString="Webb, M. D. &amp; Vilbaste, J. (1994) Review of the leafhopper genus Balclutha Kirkaldy in the Oriental Region (Insecta: Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 56, 56 - 86." type="journal article" year="1994">Webb &amp; Vilbaste (1994)</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1781,2022]" pageId="3" pageNumber="497">Male genitalia. Pygofer tapered posteriorly to acute process and produced moderately posteriorly with a small process dorsally. Valve broad, triangular. Subgenital plate with basal lobe-like area elongate, distal finger-like area very short; small dorsal sclerotized lobe basally. Style lateral lobe elongate. Connective with stem similar in length to arms. Aedeagus with broad socle and strongly sinuate elongate shaft in lateral view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
